cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on cooperative control of mobile manipulators, which is a core topic in robotics. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a set of distributed adaptive controllers to achieve motion synchronization of the mobile manipulator ensemble, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a networked system of mobile manipulators, which can be considered as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an adaptation-based estimation law for each robotic agent to estimate the desired local trajectory, which involves AI techniques. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, the proposed adaptation-based estimation law can be seen as a form of online learning.
